/* CannonadeCommand GLOBAL hook for the VM-tab stylesheet. Registered under
   Menu="Buttons" so Unraid AUTO-INJECTS the same-basename sheet
   (sheets/CannonadeCommand.VmTab.css) into the <head> of EVERY page — exactly like
   the Header/Shares/SettingsGrid hooks. That is the ONLY reliable way to load it:
   the VM area's own CannonadeCommand.VMs.page is Menu="VMs" (title-less injector for
   vms.js) and a manual <link> there does NOT load, which is why the VM-tab CSS
   (badges + alignment) never applied. All rules are gated behind html.cc-vms-on,
   which vms.js sets only when the VM area + master theming are on, so this sheet is
   inert on every other page. Link="cc-vmtab-hook" renders a bare <div> instead of a
   visible CC menu icon (we only restyle, never add an icon).

   vms.js is ALSO loaded here (not from a Menu="VMs" page): Unraid's /VMs page is
   Tabs="true", so a title-less child page goes through the tabbed layout's inline-eval
   branch — which does NOT execute a <script> tag (dynamically eval'd markup never runs
   script elements). That is why the whole VM enhancer was inert ("VM tab completely
   unchanged"): vms.js never ran, so html.cc-vms-on was never set and this sheet couldn't
   apply. Loading it from this Buttons hook puts it in the <head> of every page like
   header.js/shares.js, bypassing the inline-eval branch entirely. vms.js self-gates to
   /VMs, so it is inert elsewhere. */
?>
